            <notesStmt>
                <note type="summary">
                    
                        <p>Letter from Edward D. Stone, Rector of Coolock in Dublin to the under secretary, Sir Robert Chalmers (1858-1938). Chalmers succeeded Sir Matthew Nathan who resigned on 3 May 1916 in due to his failure to prevent the Rising. </p>
                    
                        <p></p>
                    
                        <p>Rev. Stone is writing on behalf of his sister who is claiming compensation for her bicycle which was left in a shop in Lower Abbey Street for repair before Easter. It was  destroyed during the Rising.</p>
                    
                </note>
